      "content": "The process isn't about \"fixing\" you but rather navigating a radical re-birth where the pain itself reveals where you must go next; even when it feels futile, the act of breathing persists because the sensation of existing is the only proof that anything is left to change. That belief that misery will only drag out is a defense mechanism to soothe the terror of being truly honest about not wanting to try anymore.",
